record_data.record_plain_text:
1. Availability: Spring Valley Wind LLC ("Spring Valley") makes electric energy and capacity available under this Tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below.
2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all wholesale sales of electric energy and capacity by Spring Valley at market-based rates.
3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Spring Valley.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Spring Valley.
5. Seller Category: Spring Valley is a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 CFR ? 35.36(a), in the following regions: Northwest, Southeast, Central, Southwest Power Pool, and Southwest. Spring Valley is a Category 2 seller in the Northeast region.
6. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Spring Valley shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Spring Valley's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Spring Valley to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Spring Valley's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Spring Valley's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff.
7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Spring Valley has received waiver of: Subparts B and C of Part 35, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41, Part 101, and Part 141, except sections 141.14 and 141.15.; and received blanket approval under Part 34. Spring Valley Wind LLC, Docket No. ER12-726-001 (2012) (unpublished letter order).
